    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Office of the Jewish Messenger</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>119 West Houston Street</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>May 10th 1864</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Esteemed Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">The Bible &amp; prayer<lb/> books reached us yesterday<lb/> in good
                order.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As regards the<lb/>
                <add>Hebrew</add> you inquired about, the<lb/> prices are $12 and $25.— to<lb/> you,
                $10 and $22. Are these<lb/> rates conformable to your expecta<lb/>tions? If so, let
                us know<lb/> &amp; the number you order will<lb/> be promptly forwarded.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We sympathize in<lb/> your recital concerning advanced<lb/> rates of
                labor. There appears to<lb/> be no help for it. We can only submit.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My father desires me to<lb/> say that he knows nothing<lb/> whatever
                of the matter you<lb/> refer to, concerning the inquiry<lb/> put to him by
                    <persName>Mr Solis</persName>. He<lb/> is entirely ignorant of the affair<lb/>
                and has not been applied to by<lb/> anybody with reference to it. He<lb/> says that
                he “thought you knew<lb/> him better than to put such<lb/> a question.”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With respect to the Board of<lb/> Delegates, I can inform you<lb/>
                of one accession—that of the<lb/>
                <placeName>Clinton St.</placeName> congregation of this city.<lb/> I am trying to
                bring the others<lb/> in, but the <persName>Wise</persName>-Germanic influence<lb/>
                is too strong. If you have drafted<lb/> any document you would like to<lb/> have
                issued, you might send it<lb/> to me as soon as you please<lb/> There will be a
                meeting of the</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Executive Committee in a week or two.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The Free School movement has<lb/> progressed quite favorably.
                Some<lb/> 400 members at $5 a year have been<lb/> reported by the Presidents of five
                congrega<lb/>tions &amp; two of these will increase their<lb/> lists to 200 each,
                while an aggregate<lb/> of 1000 is confidently looked for<lb/> in a very few weeks.
                Donations, also,<lb/> are coming in rapidly. I think<lb/> they will have at least 2
                schools<lb/> open in <date>September</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Trusting you are quite well,<lb/> and expecting to see you
                before<lb/> many weeks at <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> if not here I am
                Rev &amp; dear sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M. J. Isaacs</persName>.</p>
            <p>My parents &amp; <persName>Jacob</persName> wish to<lb/> be remembered.</p>
            <p>Please to send me <hi rend="underline">at once</hi> to<lb/>
                <placeName>150 Nassau Street</placeName>, <hi rend="underline">and not to</hi></p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p><hi rend="underline"><placeName>Houston St.</placeName></hi> as I don't wish<lb/>
                father to know anything about<lb/> it, a copy of your Bible<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">unbound</hi> &amp; on the best paper.<lb/> I intend it as a
                present to<lb/> my parents for their <hi rend="underline">silver</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">wedding</hi>, and wish to have it<lb/> bound under my own eye
                in<lb/> a style that may not be<lb/> always ready at your binder's.<lb/> (with all
                due respect to <persName>Che<add>?</add></persName>)<lb/> Please send it without
                fail<lb/> to <persName>M. S. Isaacs</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <placeName>150 Nassau St.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <placeName>N.Y.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>by Express</p>
        </body>
